'''Abell 2261''' is one of 25 [[galaxy cluster]]s being studied as part of the [[Cluster Lensing And Supernova survey with Hubble]] (CLASH) program, a major project to build a library of scientific data on lensing clusters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/hubble/science/a2261-bcg.html|title=NASA - Monster Galaxy May Have Been Stirred Up By Black-hole Mischief|date=October 25, 2012|website=www.nasa.gov|language=en|access-date=2016-07-15}}</ref>

It also has the galaxy [[A2261-BCG]] (short for Abell 2261 Brightest Cluster Galaxy) which has the largest galaxy core ever observed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.space.com/18226-giant-galaxy-core-black-hole-hubble.html|title=Monster Galaxy's Core Is Biggest Ever Seen|date=October 26, 2012|website=www.space.com|access-date=2016-07-15}}</ref>
